content.text:
## Summary

**ResetPassword.tsx** — Full component overview:
- Validates recovery token via `onAuthStateChange` event ("PASSWORD_RECOVERY") and URL hash check (`type=recovery`)
- If token invalid/expired, shows "Invalid Reset Link" card with redirect to login
- Password validation enforces: 8+ chars, uppercase, lowercase, digit, special char
- On submit: calls `supabase.auth.updateUser({ password })`, then navigates to `/kira`
- Toast notifications for both success and errors
- Shows live password requirement checklist as user types

**Auth.tsx** — Sign-in error handling (lines 236–250) and toast import:

**Toast import:** (line 9)
```javascript
import { useToast } from "@/hooks/use-toast";
```

**Sign-in error block (else branch, lines 236–254):**
```javascript
} else {
  const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signInWithPassword({
    email: email.trim(),
    password,
  });

  if (error) {
    const msg = error.message.toLowerCase();
    if (msg.includes("invalid login") || msg.includes("invalid credentials") || msg.includes("wrong password")) {
      toast({ title: "Incorrect email or password", description: "Please check your details and try again.", variant: "destructive" });
    } else if (msg.includes("email not confirmed")) {
      toast({ title: "Email not confirmed", description: "Please check your inbox and click the confirmation link we sent you.", variant: "destructive" });
    } else {
      toast({ title: "Sign in failed", description: error.message, variant: "destructive" });
    }
  } else if (data.user) {
    toast({ title: "Welcome back!", description: "Good to see you." });
  }
}
```

**Regarding "different provider (Google)" detection:** There is NO existing logic to detect this scenario. The sign-in error handling only catches:
- Invalid credentials ("invalid login", "wrong password")
